					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">I think the proper way, or one of them, to put sprites off-screen is to set the Y value to $F0. Alternatively you could just write $F0 to all of Sprite RAM. Atleast I seem to recall alot of games doing this. I guess that $F0 and up would all hide it. You don't want to put them horizontally off screen and not also vertically since the sprites would still count torward the 8 sprite scanline limit.</div>

